Injecting Dependencies Using @Qualifier (Resolving Bean Conflicts):

When you have multiple beans of the same type, Spring doesn’t know which one to inject. Use
@Qualifier to specify exactly which bean you want.

How it works:

Annotate your bean with a unique name using @Component("beanName") or @Bean("beanName").
Use @Qualifier("beanName") where you inject the dependency.
Example:

Define multiple beans:

@Component("mysqlRepository")
public class MySQLUserRepository implements UserRepository { }

@Component("mongoRepository")
public class MongoUserRepository implements UserRepository { }

Inject with @Qualifier:

@Component
public class UserService {
    private final UserRepository userRepository;

    @Autowired
    public UserService(@Qualifier("mysqlRepository") UserRepository userRepository) {
        this.userRepository = userRepository;
    }
}

Summary Table:

Situation	                                         Solution

Only one bean of a type                         	 @Autowired is enough
Multiple beans of the same type	                     Use @Qualifier
